HOUSE . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . No. 254
By Representative Kerans of Danvers, a petition (accompanied by bill, House, No. 254) of Sally
P. Kerans and others for legislation to replace stolen transitional assistance financial assistance
program benefits. Children, Families and Persons with Disabilities.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act to replace stolen benefits.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 2 of chapter 18 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 subsection (B)(s), the following new subsection:-
3 Subsection (t). promptly replace the full amount of financial assistance or nutrition
4 benefits stolen through electronic benefit transfer card skimming, card cloning or other
5 fraudulent methods, including organized identity theft schemes, to the extent the federal
6 government fails to provide federal funds to replace stolen benefits, provided that the thefts have
7 been reported to or identified by the Department in accordance with procedures for making and
8 verifying replacement claims established by the department.
